table.operations

Class CatColumnsOp

  • java.lang.Object
    • table.operations.CatColumnsOp
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TableOperationInterface

    public class CatColumnsOp
extends Object
implements TableOperationInterface
    The CatColumnsOp class is an operation for the MyTable.runOp() function. It concatenates the values of columns together. The getResult() method of the CatColumnsOp class returns value returns a MyTable object.
    Author:
    Saud Fatayerji

        public CatColumnsOp(String newTableName,
                    String newColName,
                    String separator,
                    String[] oldTableTitles,
                    int[] colsToJoin)
        Creates an CatColumnsOp object.
        Parameters:
        newTableName - The name for the new table.
        newColName - The title of the column that will be created.
        separator - The separator used when concatenating the values in the columns.
        oldTableTitles - The titles of the columns in the original table.
        colsToJoin - The titles of the columns to join. The order provided here will match the order that the values are joined in. These will be removed from the resulting table.
